                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <origDate notBefore="1750" notAfter="1849" evidence="lettering"/>
                            The owner of the scroll was <persName ref="PRS14028HabtaMikael">Habta Mikāʾel</persName>, whose name is written in red,
                            in the supplication formulas (even though the first part of the name is inserted over an erasure).
                        </origin>
                        <acquisition>The scroll was acquired by <persName ref="PRS14027ChristianBarth">Christian Gottlob Barth</persName> from an unknown seller 
                            (possibly a missioner), and later 
                            entred the collection of the Basler Mission. In <date>1980</date> the scroll was donated to 
                            <placeName ref="INS1001MusKulBasel">Musem of Cultures at Basle</placeName>.
                        </acquisition>
